                <pb n="1"/>
            <p>N. York Nov<hi rend="sup">er</hi> 7<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 87<lb/></p>
            <p>Mr Morais<lb/>
                Dr Sir<lb/></p>
            <p>I am very much<lb/> interested in a Fair which we<lb/> are going to hold In behalf of<lb/> our &#34;Congregation&#44; Moses MonteforeË¶<lb/> We have only been organized<lb/> two years and from only 5<lb/> members&#44; we now number 20<lb/> or more.  The room in which<lb/> the services have been held are<lb/> too small and we therefore<lb/> would like to have a place of<lb/> worship.  You have no doubt<lb/> heard of our small efforts<lb/> in your numerous visits to our<lb/> city.  My reason for thus<lb/> troubling you Dear Sir is this&#44;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="2"/>
            <p>A Gentleman of Boston&#44; Mass&#44;<lb/> has kindly sent me on a<lb/> donation and has given me<lb/> a few names of charitable men<lb/> among those is Mr Alfred Marcus<lb/> of Boston&#44; I have seen by the<lb/> Herard mention made of him<lb/> and his readiness to always<lb/> help his coreligionists.  I know<lb/> the great esteem and admiration<lb/> which Mr Marcus has expressed<lb/> for you and I take this liberty<lb/> of asking you if you will<lb/> either write him yourself in our<lb/> behalf or else give me a letter<lb/> of introduction to him.  I am<lb/> so anxious to do all in my<lb/> poor power to build up a<lb/> good Portuguese Synagogue&#45;&#45;<lb/> and would like to be the one to<lb/> have a Donation from him.<lb/>  You have doubtless forgotten<lb/> me in all these years &#38;<lb/></p>
                
                <pb n="3"/>
            <p>I am a boy of the late Mrs A. Firz&#44;<lb/> and a dear friend of the late<lb/> Miss Leah Lobo.  If I have taken<lb/> too much liberty in thus addressing<lb/> you&#44; you will pardon it in<lb/> my zeal to further the efforts of<lb/> the congregation to which I belong<lb/> in the hope of hearing from<lb/> you at your convenience<lb/> I subscribe myself<lb/> Yours very respectfully<lb/> S. A. Carr.<lb/>  ne&#233; Carvalho&#44;<lb/> No 60. E. 109<hi rend="sup">th</hi> St.<lb/> N. York.<lb/></p>
            <p>Executive Committee<lb/> A. M. Larado<lb/> G. S. Rosenberg<lb/> Dr Hartogensis<lb/> H. Pariente<lb/> Isidore Osario&#44;<lb/> Rev. M. Lenedalia.<lb/></p>
            </body>
